Pork bone soup (or literally potato soup "gamjatang" is the Korean translation) is the best. Easily feeds 3-4 people. The kimchi is surprisingly robust. I eat it all every time. We call ahead and pick it up for dinner (let them know you'll just heat it up at home). Highly recommended.
We were super intrigued to find a traditional Korean restaurant that served more than just your basic tofu soup and short ribs. Authentic Korean Food. That actually reminds you of South Korea.
One and only spot serving authentic & flavorful Korean food in the bay area. All time my favorite. Highly recommend!
Our go for spot for lunch. if you look for a authentic Korean food, this is the one.

My all time favorite spot for Korean food. Very authentic, savory and flavorful food! My recommendation list: Beef short rib soup, spicy braised beef short ribs, steamed pork belly, braised pork trotters, and sauteed spicy baby octopus.
Excellent food and service. A new favorite.
